    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on Effectiveness of Derivatives on Hedging</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Gayathri Selvarajan</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Derivatives on Hedging</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2010 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P4624</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">The main objective of this project is to study the effectiveness of derivatives using hedging strategy.Derivatives today have become an integral part of the financial system of a country as well as at the international level. They have influenced almost every aspect of capital and money markets all over the world ranging from investing, raising of funds and managing the risk.Financial derivatives like options, futures, forwards and swaps have emerged in the financial market to handle and manage such risk. New products and strategies are being developed at the fast rate in order to cope with the changing environment.
Today the corporate units operate in a complex business environment. Managements often find that the profitability of their organization heavily depends upon factors which are beyond their control. Important among these are external influences like commodity prices, stock prices, interest rates, exchange rates etc. As a result, modern business has become more complex, uncertain and risk so that the business can be run successful. An important function of hedging is to reduce or control risk by transferring it to others who are willing to bear risk. So the activity of trading with the objectives of reducing or controlling risk is called hedging.
The first chapter explains about the derivatives market, company profile, problem identified and also explains about the scope of the research.
Second Chapter is about the Literature Survey which explains the various researchersâ€™ views about this particular topic.
Third Chapter explains about the Research methodology used in the research. The research design used is Descriptive research, as it is started from the scrap from Collection of questionnaire.
Fourth chapter gives the detailed analysis of the project with various tables, Charts and graphs.
The Fifth chapter concludes with the various findings as listed out and suggestions are given to solve the identified problem.If the suggested measures are taken, the efforts will be much appreciated by the customers and the customers will be more loyal towards the organization.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8189">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8189</a></td></tr>
